attributes.label: Gene biotype
attributes.description: Gene or transcript classification annotated in Ensembl

attributes.label: Chromosome
attributes.description: Chromosome where a gene is located

attributes.label: # of exons
attributes.description: Number of exons for each transcript of each gene

attributes.label: # of paralogs
attributes.description: Number of duplicated genes (paralogs) in each human gene calculated based on HomoloGene

attributes.label: Evolutionary divergence
attributes.description: Most distant organisms from human that have orthologous genes in HomoloGene

attributes.label: High-level expression
attributes.description: Tissues in which a gene was tissue-specific highly expressed only in one of 34 tissues of RefEx

dataSource.label: Calculations for tissue specificity of genechip human GSE7307 from RefEx

attributes.label: Low-level expression
attributes.description: Tissues in which a gene was tissue-specific lowly expressed only in one of 34 tissues of RefEx

dataSource.label: Calculations for tissue specificity of genechip human GSE7307 from RefEx

attributes.label: Expressed in tissues
attributes.description: Tissues in which a gene is tissue-specific highly expressed in 48 tissues of GTEx

dataSource.label: Supplementary Table 1 of A systematic survey of human tissue-specific gene expression and splicing reveals new opportunities for therapeutic target identification and evaluation; R. Y. Yang et al.; bioRxiv 311563

attributes.label: Not expressed in tissues
attributes.description: Tissues in which expression of a gene is not detected in 48 tissues of GTEx

dataSource.label: Supplementary Table 1 of A systematic survey of human tissue-specific gene expression and splicing reveals new opportunities for therapeutic target identification and evaluation; R. Y. Yang et al.; bioRxiv 311563

attributes.label: Transcription factors
attributes.description: Transcription factors with predicted target genes in ChIP-Atlas

attributes.label: Protein domains
attributes.description: Protein domains from UniProt

attributes.label: Cellular component
attributes.description: Functional annotations (GO terms) derived from the Cellular component category of GeneOntology, which Uniprot has assigned to each human protein with evidence information

attributes.label: Biological process
attributes.description: Functional annotations (GO terms) derived from the Biological process category of GeneOntology, which Uniprot has assigned to each human protein with evidence information

attributes.label: Molecular function
attributes.description: Functional annotations (GO terms) derived from the Molecular function category of GeneOntology, which Uniprot has assigned to each human protein with evidence information

attributes.label: Ligands
attributes.description: Classification by non-protein molecules which bind/react with proteins in Function section from UniProt

attributes.label: Molecular mass
attributes.description: Molecular weight of the protein including information from multiple isoforms in Sequences section from UniProt

attributes.label: PTMs
attributes.description: Classification by types of post-translational modifications, including S-S bonds (disulfide bonds) in Amino acid modifications section from UniProt

attributes.label: # of transmembrane domains
attributes.description: Number of transmembrane domains. A group of molecules forming a family, such as channels, may have the same number of domains in Topology section from UniProt

attributes.label: # of phosphorylation sites
attributes.description: Number of phosphorylation at Ser/Thr/Tyr, which may create an activation state for the protein and acts like a switch in Amino acid modifications section from UniProt

attributes.label: # of glycosylation sites
attributes.description: Number of glycosylation sites, including N-linked,O-linked and others in Amino acid modifications section from UniProt

attributes.label: Disease-related proteins
attributes.description: Disease-related proteins in Pathology & Biotech section from UniProt

attributes.label: Tissues w/expression reported
attributes.description: Classification based on the name of the tissue from which the clone was isolated in the reference describing the protein sequence in Tissue section from UniProt

attributes.label: Evidence of existence
attributes.description: Classification by the basis of protein expression, such as whether it has been identified as a protein or transcript in Expression section from neXtProt

attributes.label: Structure data existence
attributes.description: Uniprot entries having 3D structure data in PDB in Structure section from Uniprot

attributes.label: # of alpha-helices
attributes.description: Number of 'Helix' entities counted in each entry of PDB

attributes.label: # of beta-sheets
attributes.description: Number of 'Sheet' entities counted in each entry of PDB

attributes.label: # of peptides in a PDB entry
attributes.description: The number of peptides in a PDB entry

attributes.label: Other related molecules
attributes.description: Nonpeptide molecules related protein structures including water, metal ions, and low molecular weight compounds such as glycerol used to make crystals

attributes.label: Analysis methods
attributes.description: Classification by the method used to determine the three-dimensional structure in Experimental method section from PDB

attributes.label: Crystallization temperature
attributes.description: Temperature of the crystallization solution obtained in Crystallization Conditions section from PDB

attributes.label: Crystallization pH
attributes.description: pH value of the crystallization solution in Crystallization Conditions section from PDB

attributes.label: Proteins in pathway
attributes.description: Proteins participating as components classified by pathway (reaction) from Reactome

attributes.label: Compounds in pathway
attributes.description: Compounds participating as components classified by pathway (reaction) from Reactome

attributes.label: # of interacting proteins
attributes.description: Classification of uniprot proteins by the number of target proteins they interact with in Interaction section from UniProt

attributes.label: ChEMBL assay existence
attributes.description: Uniprot entries classified according to the presence or absence of a method to detect direct protein-compound interactions (ChEMBL assay)

attributes.label: Substance type
attributes.description: Classification based on the type of drug, such as compound or nucleic acid drugs from ChEMBL

attributes.label: Chemical role
attributes.description: Classification based on the chemical roles, such as antioxidant or environmental contaminant from ChEBI

attributes.label: Application type
attributes.description: Classification based on the application types, such as pharmaceutical or pesticide from ChEBI

attributes.label: Action type
attributes.description: Classification based on the mechanism of action, such as an inhibitor or an antagonist from ChEMBL

attributes.label: Biological role
attributes.description: Classification based on the biological roles, such as inhibitor or antimicrobial agent from ChEBI

attributes.label: Drug indication
attributes.description: Classification of diseases for which drugs are indicated, based on hierarchical data using MeSH, a life science thesaurus from ChEMBL

attributes.label: Drug development phase
attributes.description: Classification based on the drug's development phase (research stage, phase I-III, and post-launch) from ChEMBL

attributes.label: PubChem ATC classification
attributes.description: Classification of a medicine (in PubChem) according to its medicinal properties (WHO ATC Code)

attributes.label: ChEMBL ATC classification
attributes.description: Classification of a medicine (in ChEMBL) according to its medicinal properties (WHO ATC Code)

attributes.label: Diseases in Mondo
attributes.description: Subcategories in the Disease or disorder category in the Mondo Disease Ontology (Mondo)

attributes.label: Diseases in MeSH
attributes.description: Subcategories in the Disease category in Medical Subject Headings (MeSH)

attributes.label: Diseases in NANDO
attributes.description: Japanese rare and intractable disease categories in the Nanbyo Disease Ontology (NANDO)

attributes.label: Cross referenced disease DBs in Mondo
attributes.description: Number of entries linked to Mondo in each of approx. 70 disease related databases from database cross reference in Mondo

attributes.label: Phenotypic abnormality
attributes.description: Classification the subcategories of the Phenotypic abnormality categories of the Human Phenotype Ontology (HPO)

attributes.label: GWAS
attributes.description: Classification of statistically significant variants in genome-wide association studies (GWAS) based on associated traits. Obtained from GWAS catalog via TogoVar

attributes.label: Clinical significance
attributes.description: Classification of variants according to their clinical significance, such as whether they are the cause of the disease or not. Obtained from ClinVar via TogoVar
